                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d851">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Draper</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-03-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 16, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. Hay directs that proper authorities be informed of the expected arrival of
                    the U. S. S. <hi rend="italic">Dixie</hi> at Naples April 6, Venice April 30,
                    and Livorno May 9; and that port courtesies usual in such cases be
                    suggested.)</p>
            </div>
